"title": "4155: divination",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "4155",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Attempts to discover the unknown or the future by supernatural means, involving communication with the spirit world.  It is expressly forbidden by God and has disastrous consequences.</p>\n<h2>Divination was part of early beliefs and practices</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen41:24\">GEN 41:24</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod7:11\">EXO 7:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa31:1-Isa31:2\">ISA 31:1–31:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa47:9\">ISA 47:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer27:9\">JER 27:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek21:21\">EZK 21:21</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan2:2\">DAN 2:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan5:7\">DAN 5:7</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of divination in NT times</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts8:9-Acts8:13\">ACT 8:9–8:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts8:18-Acts8:24\">ACT 8:18–8:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:6-Acts13:12\">ACT 13:6–13:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:16-Acts16:18\">ACT 16:16–16:18</a></p>\n<h2>The reality of a supernatural spirit world</h2>\n<h3>The spirit world is real and alluring</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts8:11\">ACT 8:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen44:5\">GEN 44:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen44:15\">GEN 44:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam6:2\">1SA 6:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts8:9-Acts8:10\">ACT 8:9–8:10</a></p>\n<h3>The spirit world is powerful and dangerous</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs9:22\">2KI 9:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num22:6-Num22:7\">NUM 22:6–22:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num22:12\">NUM 22:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs17:17\">2KI 17:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech10:2\">ZEC 10:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph6:12\">EPH 6:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess2:9-2Thess2:10\">2TH 2:9–2:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev18:23\">REV 18:23</a></p>\n<h2>Deliberate involvement with divination forbidden</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:31\">LEV 19:31</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod22:18\">EXO 22:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:26\">LEV 19:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut18:10-Deut18:14\">DEU 18:10–18:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs21:6\">2KI 21:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa8:19-Isa8:20\">ISA 8:19–8:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek13:23\">EZK 13:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic5:12\">MIC 5:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal3:5\">MAL 3:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:20\">GAL 5:20</a></p>\n<h2>It is God's divine privilege to reveal or conceal things</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut29:29\">DEU 29:29</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov25:2\">PRO 25:2</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of the evil of divination</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam28:7\">1SA 28:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam28:3-1Sam28:15\">1SA 28:3–28:15</a></p>\n<h2>Casting lots to make decisions</h2>\n<p>Divination is clearly forbidden but some practices such as casting lots seem acceptable ways of discovering God's will in particular circumstances:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr26:13-1Chr26:16\">1CH 26:13–26:16</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh11:1\">NEH 11:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:26\">ACT 1:26</a></p>",
